ichmond </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Va. </LOCATION>, bureau after working for The Ledger in <LOCATION> Lakeland </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Fla. </LOCATION>, and for The Orlando Sentinel. In subsequent years, he served as an AP newsman in <LOCATION> Washington </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Los </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Angeles </LOCATION>, and in <LOCATION> Saigon </LOCATION> during the Vietnam War. <PERSON> Williams </PERSON>, 39, has been a member of <ORGANIZATION> AP </ORGANIZATION>'s national editing staff in <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION> since 1984. He has supervised filing of the national news report, and handled feature writing assignments. <PERSON> Williams </PERSON> joined the <ORGANIZATION> AP </ORGANIZATION> at <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Orleans </LOCATION> in 1978 after work as a reporter for <ORGANIZATION> The </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Fitchburg-Leominster </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Sentinel </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; Enterprise in <LOCATION> Fitchburg </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Mass </LOCATION>.
