<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Rep. <PERSON> Mickey </PERSON> <PERSON> Leland </PERSON>'s crusade against hunger will live on despite his death, says <ORGANIZATION> House </ORGANIZATION> Speaker <PERSON> Thomas </PERSON> <PERSON> S. </PERSON> <PERSON> Foley </PERSON>, but there appears to be no obvious successor to carry the torch. `` There will be a determination on the part of members of the <ORGANIZATION> House </ORGANIZATION> to work for those goals that <PERSON> Mickey </PERSON> <PERSON> Leland </PERSON> sought to achieve _ the alleviation of hunger and suffering here and in <LOCATION> Africa </LOCATION> and elsewhere in the world,'' <PERSON> Foley </PERSON> said Monday. However, <PERSON> Foley </PERSON>, D-Wash., did n't say who would become chairman of the <ORGANIZATION> House </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Select </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Committee </ORGANIZATION> on Hunger, the panel <PERSON> Leland </PERSON> founded in 1984 <PERSON> Leland </PERSON>, a <LOCATION> Texas </LOCATION> Democrat, died in a plane crash last week while on a fact-finding mission in <LOCATION> Ethiopia </LOCATION>. <PERSON> Foley </PERSON> aide <PERSON> Jeff </PERSON> <PERSON> Biggs </PERSON> said a new committee chairman was not expected to be named until next month when <ORGANIZATION> Congress </ORGANIZATION> returns from a month-long recess. <PERSON> Leland </PERSON>'s efforts were credited with getting $ 800 million in relief for victims of famine in <LOCATION> Africa </LOCATION>. `` Whenever a member wanted to do something -LRB- on hunger -RRB- they would go to him,'' <PERSON> Miranda </PERSON> <PERSON> Katsoyannis </PERSON>, chief of staff of the hunger committee, said Monday. `` This committee served as a focus. The <ORGANIZATION> Congress </ORGANIZATION> became more sensitive as a result.'' <PERSON> Leland </PERSON> parceled out responsibilities and several members of the committee were leaders in specific areas, <PERSON> Katsoyannis </PERSON> said. The senior member is Rep. <PERSON> Tony </PERSON> <PERSON> Hall </PERSON>, <LOCATION> D-Ohio </LOCATION>, who shared <PERSON> Leland </PERSON>'s concern for hunger in the Third World Rep. <PERSON> Gary </PERSON> <PERSON> Ackerman </PERSON>, <LOCATION> D-N.Y. </LOCATION>, another committee member, was one of <PERSON> Leland </PERSON>'s closest associates and among the first to go to <LOCATION> Ethiopia </LOCATION> to strengthen search efforts last week. Rep. <PERSON> Byron </PERSON> <PERSON> Dorgan </PERSON>, <LOCATION> D-N.D. </LOCATION>, is known for his work with the hungry of <LOCATION> Central </LOCATION> <LOCATION> America </LOCATION>, while Rep. <PERSON> Mike </PERSON> <PERSON> Espy </PERSON>, D-Miss., has been a leader in nutrition efforts among the rural poor of the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> Rep. <PERSON> Albert </PERSON> <PERSON> Bustamante </PERSON>, <LOCATION> D-Texas </LOCATION>, is known for his work on hunger problems among the Hispanic poor. Seniority rules do n't apply to select committee chairmanships which, like standing committees, are made by the speaker. Select committees do n't act on legislation, but do initiate studies, hold hearings and influence other committees to make changes or additions to the federal statutes. `` Select committees at their best, offer us a flexibility and a sense of focus that we may otherwise not find in our standing committees,'' House Republican Leader <PERSON> Bob </PERSON> <PERSON> Michel </PERSON> of <LOCATION> Illinois </LOCATION> said during debate in February on whether to continue the committees. <PERSON> Leland </PERSON> said during the same debate that his committee's work was extensive during the 100th <ORGANIZATION> Congress </ORGANIZATION>. `` Thirty-two hearings, nine basic human needs seminars and numerous briefings were held; nine reports were published and monthly status reports on international and domestic hunger were issued and widely distributed,'' he said. The House Select Committee on Hunger was instrumental in setting up the Child Survival Fund, part of the <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> foreign assistance program. It also provided impetus to expanded research into the effects of vitamin A on child mortality.
