<HEAD>11 Miners Killed in Accident; 3 Missing</HEAD>
<DATELINE>JOHANNESBURG, South Africa (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A shower of rocks in a gold mine west of <LOCATION> Johannesburg </LOCATION> killed 11 miners and left three missing, authorities said Tuesday. Six men also suffered injuries at the <LOCATION> West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Driefontein </LOCATION> mine Monday in a `` pressure burst'' _ an accident caused when a buildup of underground pressure erupts through the face of a mine shaft or tunnel, according to Gold Fields of <LOCATION> South </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Africa </LOCATION>, owner of the facility. The accident occurred at nearly 7,600 feet underground. The company said efforts to find the missing miners were continuing. <LOCATION> South </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Africa </LOCATION> has many of the deepest gold mines in the world and hundreds of miners are killed in underground accidents each year.
