a </PERSON>'s, his personal style affable rather than confrontational. At age 53, he belongs to a younger generation more receptive to change. Through 17 years in politics, however, he has been a loyal supporter of the <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Party </ORGANIZATION> _ including limited race reforms that reject majority rule. <PERSON> De </PERSON> <PERSON> Klerk </PERSON> has not set himself apart from any <PERSON> Botha </PERSON> policies and has yet to name apartheid laws he would repeal. The African <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Congress </ORGANIZATION>, the main guerrilla movement fighting white supremacy, said <PERSON> Botha </PERSON> `` dedicated his life to the construction of the apartheid system and its defense at all costs.'' `` He has brought death and destruction to millions of people in <LOCATION> South </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Africa </LOCATION> and the rest of the region ... through a systematic campaign of brutal repression,'' general secretary <PERSON> Alfred </PERSON> <PERSON> Nzo </PERSON> said in <LOCATION> Lusaka </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Zambia </LOCATION>, where the group has its headquarters. South African media also had harsh words about the former president. `` The last image that will linger for many years is that of a blind <PERSON> Samson </PERSON> who with his last strength tried to overturn the pillars of his party on himself and his own companions,'' said <ORGANIZATION> Beeld </ORGANIZATION>, an Afrikaans-language daily that had supported <PERSON> Botha </PERSON>. Although the <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Party </ORGANIZATION> is favored in next month's elections, it is expected to lose ground to both the anti-apartheid <ORGANIZATION> Democratic </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Party </ORGANIZATION> on its left and the segregationist <ORGANIZATION> Conservative </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Party </ORGANIZATION> on its right. <PERSON> De </PERSON> <PERSON> Klerk