<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Business inventories rose 0.4 percent in June as business sales fell 0.3 percent, the government said. Analysts said the report indicated slow but continued economic growth with low inflation. Inventories often rise during periods of slow economic growth as production exceeds demand, a process that sometimes leads to a loss of jobs as businesses cut their output. Economists, however, said the inventories reported Monday are not unusually large in proportion to sales.
</TEXT>
