N> Dorfman </PERSON> also denied that he had been a party to any manipulation. `` I'm so careful and sensitive about what I do,'' he said Monday night when reached at his home for comment. <PERSON> Dorfman </PERSON>, who also is a commentator on <ORGANIZATION> Cable </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> News </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Network </ORGANIZATION>'s `` Moneyline'' program, said he knew nothing about any investigation `` I have not been contacted by the <ORGANIZATION> SEC </ORGANIZATION>, the <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Stock </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION> or anybody else,'' he said. `` I think it's a lot of crap.'' <PERSON> Tom </PERSON> <PERSON> Petruno </PERSON>, <PERSON> Dorfman </PERSON>'s editor at <ORGANIZATION> USA </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Today </ORGANIZATION>, also said he knew of no investigation. `` We have no idea where <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> News got this information or who its sources are,'' he said. A spokesman for the <ORGANIZATION> SEC </ORGANIZATION> told the magazine that the agency could not confirm or deny any such investigation.
