ON> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION>. President <PERSON> Fred </PERSON> <PERSON> Salerno </PERSON> called the accident `` tragic'' and asked the union to resume negotiations `` to try and calm the waters. In other incidents: _ A <ORGANIZATION> NYNEX </ORGANIZATION> car was burned shortly after midnight Monday in a company parking lot in <LOCATION> Elmont </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> N.Y. </LOCATION> Police said the fire was suspicious. _ Four strikers were arrested at a <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION> Telephone facility in <LOCATION> Catskill </LOCATION>, 40 miles south of <LOCATION> Albany </LOCATION>, when they ignored police barricades. _ Two people were arrested outside <LOCATION> Michigan </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Bell </LOCATION> offices in the <LOCATION> Detroit </LOCATION> suburb of <LOCATION> Southfield </LOCATION>. Officer <PERSON> Gary </PERSON> <PERSON> Conat </PERSON> said one allegedly obstructed a police officer, but he was n't sure about allegations against the other. _ Toll and 911 service was cut off to about 8,000 customers in <LOCATION> West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Virginia </LOCATION> after vandals cut 11 cables. Residents in the area are still able to dial police or fire directly, C & amp; P Telephone of <LOCATION> West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Virginia </LOCATION> said.
