/ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Airlines </ORGANIZATION>. In addition to <PERSON> Davis </PERSON>; <ORGANIZATION> Kohlberg </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Kravis </ORGANIZATION>, <PERSON> Forstmann </PERSON> <PERSON> Little </PERSON> and <ORGANIZATION> Pan </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Am </ORGANIZATION> were among those who unsuccessfully made takeover proposals for <ORGANIZATION> NWA </ORGANIZATION>, which was sold to a group headed by <LOCATION> Los </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Angeles </LOCATION> investor <PERSON> Alfred </PERSON> <PERSON> Checchi </PERSON> for $ 3.65 billion. Officials of <ORGANIZATION> UAL </ORGANIZATION> refused to comment Monday on the report of additional bidders. `` We neither confirm or deny any other bids,'' <ORGANIZATION> UAL </ORGANIZATION> spokesman <PERSON> Doughty </PERSON> said Monday. <PERSON> Kohlberg </PERSON> <PERSON> Kravis </PERSON> <PERSON> Roberts </PERSON> also remained silent on the issue. `` The firm has said nothing and have n't made any comment'' on whether it is interested in acquiring <ORGANIZATION> UAL </ORGANIZATION>, said spokesman <PERSON> Tom </PERSON> <PERSON> Daly </PERSON>. Officials of <PERSON> Forstmann </PERSON> <PERSON> Little </PERSON> also declined comment. <ORGANIZATION> Pan </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Am </ORGANIZATION> said it would make an offer if <ORGANIZATION> UAL </ORGANIZATION>'s board asked it to. `` They have not publicly said they were up for sale,'' said <ORGANIZATION> Pan </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Am </ORGANIZATION> spokeswoman <PERSON> Elizabeth </PERSON> <PERSON> Manners </PERSON>. `` My understanding is that they did say they were going to explore some alternative.'' Last week, in response to <PERSON> Davis </PERSON>' overture, <ORGANIZATION> UAL </ORGANIZATION>'s board of directors announced it would explore all possible financial and strategic alternatives open to the company.
